The testcase tests the installation and basic functionality of a Frontend. You will need a MythTV backend in the network to do this testcase completely.

Ensure installation is finished (1)
Ensure the machine boots up (2)
<dl>
    <dt>Go though the Ubiquity install as you would any other install. Most options won't matter for this testcase, but be sure to choose the following options</dt>'
        <dd>
            <ul>
                <li title="Specified Setting">Do NOT name the user mythtv</li>
                <li title="Specified Setting">Automatic (Guided) Partitioning</li>
                <li title="Specified Setting">"Frontend"</li>
                <li title="Specified Setting">If you have no remote, choose no remote suppport</li>
                <li title="Specified Setting">For the security key, enter the PIN from the backend (in the backend testcase, this is set to 1234)</li>
            </ul>
        </dd>
    <dt>remove the installation media and reboot. (1)</dt>
    <dt>it should boot into the frontend. (2)</dt>
    <dt>Select</dt>
	<dt>"Watch TV". (this will</dt>
	<dt>only work if you have a backend already in the network)</dt>
        <dd>The demo video should start playing.</dd>
</dl>
[False Condition] 
<dl>
    <dt>Go though the Ubiquity install as you would any other install. Most options won't matter for this testcase, but be sure to choose the following options</dt>'
        <dd>
            <ul>
                <li title="Specified Setting">Do NOT name the user mythtv</li>
                <li title="Specified Setting">Automatic (Guided) Partitioning</li>
                <li title="Specified Setting">"Frontend"</li>
                <li title="Specified Setting">If you have no remote, choose no remote suppport</li>
                <li title="Specified Setting">For the security key, enter the PIN from the backend (in the backend testcase, this is set to 1234)</li>
            </ul>
        </dd>
    <dt>remove the installation media and reboot. (1)</dt>
</dl>

